<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header reveal">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Soren</span>
      <h2>A Discord event calendar built for active communities</h2>
      <p>Most servers need more than a static calendar link. Soren keeps the entire event workflow inside Discord so members can discover, RSVP, get reminded, and show up without leaving the server.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid-2" style="gap:var(--space-5);">
      <div class="card card-hover reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="feature-icon">📅</div>
        <h4>Calendar-style event management in Discord</h4>
        <p>Create events with <code>/newevent</code>, publish them to any channel, add descriptions, start and end times, timezone support, notify roles, recurrence, RSVP limits, and cutoff times.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card card-hover reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="feature-icon">✅</div>
        <h4>Live RSVP buttons and attendee lists</h4>
        <p>Members click Accept, Tentative, or Decline directly on the event embed. Soren updates attendee lists in real time and lets each member check their own upcoming events with <code>/myevents</code>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card card-hover reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="feature-icon">⏰</div>
        <h4>Discord event reminders that survive restarts</h4>
        <p>Schedule multiple reminders per event and ping the right roles before start time. Reminder state is stored in the database, so planned notices remain reliable after bot restarts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card card-hover reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="feature-icon">🔁</div>
        <h4>Recurring Discord events</h4>
        <p>Run weekly raids, monthly meetings, daily sessions, bi-weekly events, or custom recurrence intervals. Soren advances recurring events automatically and posts each new occurrence.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card card-hover reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="feature-icon">🗓️</div>
        <h4>Google Calendar and ICS support</h4>
        <p>Sync Discord events with Google Calendar, post weekly calendar digest summaries to channels, and export upcoming events as an <code>.ics</code> file for Google Calendar, Apple Calendar, and Outlook.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card card-hover reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="feature-icon">📋</div>
        <h4>Waitlists, cutoff times, and discussion threads</h4>
        <p>Cap accepted RSVPs, automatically queue overflow signups, close RSVPs after a deadline, and keep event-specific planning in dedicated Discord threads.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--dark">
  <div class="container">
